üìò Security Concepts ‚Äì PG-DITISS (Aug 2025)
Session 3: Web App Risks, Risk Identification, Threat Modeling, HTTP Fields, Burp Suite
üîπ BASIC MCQs (10)
1. Web application security risks mainly arise due to:
A. Hardware failure
B. Poor coding and configuration
C. Power outage
D. ISP issues

2. Which organization maintains a list of common web application risks?
A. ISO
B. NIST
C. CERT-In
D. OWASP

3. Identifying application security risks involves:
A. Writing new code
B. Finding vulnerabilities and threats
C. Encrypting data
D. Blocking IPs

4. Threat modeling helps in:
A. Code compilation
B. Identifying potential attackers and attack paths
C. Network routing
D. Patch management

5. Which HTTP field identifies the client software?
A. Host
B. Referer
C. User-Agent
D. Cookie

6. Which HTTP header is used to send session information?
A. Accept
B. Cookie
C. Content-Type
D. Connection

7. Burp Suite is mainly used for:
A. Network routing
B. Web application security testing
C. Antivirus scanning
D. Log management

8. Which Burp Suite feature intercepts HTTP requests?
A. Scanner
B. Repeater
C. Proxy
D. Decoder

9. Vulnerability scanning aims to:
A. Remove malware
B. Detect security weaknesses
C. Encrypt traffic
D. Improve performance

10. Risk in security is best defined as:
A. Threat √ó Vulnerability √ó Impact
B. Threat + Vulnerability
C. Impact √∑ Threat
D. Vulnerability ‚àí Threat

üî∏ INTERMEDIATE MCQs (10)
11. Which is NOT a web application security risk?
A. SQL Injection
B. XSS
C. Buffer Overflow
D. Power failure

12. Identifying risks requires understanding:
A. Only application code
B. Only server OS
C. Assets, threats, vulnerabilities
D. Network bandwidth

13. Threat modeling is performed:
A. After deployment only
B. During design phase
C. After incident
D. During backup

14. Which HTTP header shows the originating page?
A. Host
B. Referer
C. Origin
D. Location

15. Burp Suite Proxy works as:
A. Firewall
B. Man-in-the-middle
C. IDS
D. Load balancer

16. Which Burp tool allows modifying and resending requests?
A. Scanner
B. Proxy
C. Repeater
D. Intruder

17. Automated scanning in Burp Suite helps identify:
A. Network latency
B. Common vulnerabilities
C. Encryption keys
D. Server uptime

18. Which HTTP field specifies data format sent to server?
A. Accept
B. Content-Type
C. User-Agent
D. Cookie

19. Risk identification is ineffective without knowing:
A. IP address
B. Business impact
C. Programming language
D. Browser type

20. Burp Suite Scanner is MOST useful for:
A. Manual testing
B. Passive and active vulnerability detection
C. Traffic routing
D. Firewall bypass

üî∫ ADVANCED MCQs (10) ‚Äì CCEE HIGH-TRAP ZONE
21. Which combination BEST represents threat modeling?
A. Asset + Patch
B. Threat + Vulnerability + Impact
C. Risk + Firewall
D. Attack + Defense

22. Why threat modeling is critical before deployment?
A. Improves UI
B. Reduces future security risks
C. Speeds up execution
D. Reduces cost of server

23. Which HTTP header is MOST useful for detecting session hijacking?
A. Host
B. Cookie
C. Accept-Encoding
D. Cache-Control

24. While scanning with Burp Suite, false positives occur because:
A. Tool is outdated
B. Automated tools lack business logic context
C. Network is slow
D. SSL is enabled

25. Which Burp Suite feature is used for brute-force and fuzzing?
A. Repeater
B. Decoder
C. Intruder
D. Scanner

26. Identifying risks using tools mainly supports which security phase?
A. Prevention
B. Detection
C. Recovery
D. Response

27. HTTP headers are security-sensitive because they:
A. Control routing
B. Influence server-side behavior
C. Increase speed
D. Reduce bandwidth

28. Which lab task validates MITM capability of Burp Suite?
A. Vulnerability scanning
B. Configuring Burp with browser
C. Report generation
D. Log analysis

29. Which risk is MOST likely found via Burp Scanner?
A. Hardware failure
B. SQL Injection
C. Power outage
D. Disk crash

30. Threat modeling failure MOST commonly leads to:
A. Slow application
B. Unidentified attack vectors
C. Poor UI
D. Network congestion

